      "source": [
        "# tests_deltaV.ipynb — Suite completa de tests para δV(r)\n",
        "\n",
        "Este notebook prueba exhaustivamente la función perturbativa \(\\delta V(r)\) utilizada en la validación QNM, curvas de rotación, lentes y cúmulos.\n",
        "\n",
        "Objetivos principales:\n",
        "1. Verificar continuidad y diferenciabilidad (C¹, ideal C²).\n",
        "2. Comprobar límites físicos (horizonte y asintótico).\n",
        "3. Test de escala (invarianza con reescalado de unidades geométricas).\n",
        "4. Consistencia con el potencial de Regge–Wheeler.\n",
        "5. Robustez numérica (mallas 1k, 10k, 100k) sin NaNs/overflows.\n",
        "6. Estabilidad del valor perturbativo de δω ante refinamientos de malla.\n",
        "7. Visualizaciones y guardado de resultados.\n",
        "\n",
        "Requisitos: haber agregado `src/` con los módulos `edr_deltaV`, `edr_kerr_geometry`, `edr_modes`, `edr_potential` (si no existen, el notebook usa implementaciones fallback toy).\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Imports básicos\n",
        "import os\n",
        "import json\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from scipy.integrate import simps\n",
        "from scipy.misc import derivative\n",
        "from scipy.optimize import minimize_scalar\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 120\n",
        "\n",
        "# Intento importar funciones reales desde src/ si existen\n",
        "HAS_SRC = True\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    from edr_deltaV import deltaV as deltaV_real\n",
        "    from edr_kerr_geometry import r_plus\n",
        "    from edr_modes import psi0, normalize_psi\n",
        "    print('Módulos edr_* importados correctamente')\n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "    HAS_SRC = False\n",
        "    print('Aviso: no se importaron módulos edr_. Usando implementaciones toy.\\nError:', e)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Definiciones fallback (toy) — usadas si `src/` no está disponible\n",
        "Las versiones toy son suaves, continuas y con comportamiento físico correcto; son reemplazadas por las funciones reales cuando estén presentes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "if not HAS_SRC:\n",
        "    def r_plus(M, a):\n",
        "        return M + np.sqrt(max(M**2 - a**2, 0.0))\n",
        "\n",
        "    def deltaV_real(r, rH):\n",
        "        # toy: mezcla de potencias y decaimiento exponencial — suave y C^inf\n",
        "        r = np.array(r)\n",
        "        term1 = 0.02 * (rH / np.maximum(r, rH))**3\n",
        "        term2 = 0.01 * np.exp(-(r - rH) / 8.0)\n",
        "        term3 = 0.005 * (rH / np.maximum(r, r))**2 * np.sin((r - rH) / 2.0)\n",
        "        return term1 + term2 + term3\n",
        "\n",
        "    def psi0(r, rH):\n",
        "        r = np.array(r)\n",
        "        psi = np.exp(-0.3 * (r - rH)) * (r / rH)**2\n",
        "        return psi\n",
        "\n",
        "    def normalize_psi(r, psi):\n",
        "        N = simps(psi**2, r)\n",
        "        return psi / np.sqrt(N)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Parámetros globales para los tests\n",
        "- Usamos unidades geométricas (M = 1) para la mayoría de pruebas.\n",
        "- Se prueban diferentes espines `a` para verificar comportamiento cerca del horizonte."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "M = 1.0\n",
        "a_list = [0.0, 0.5, 0.9]\n",
        "mallas = [1000, 10000, 100000]\n",
        "results = {}\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Test 1 — Continuidad y diferenciabilidad (C¹/C²)\n",
        "Comprobamos que δV y sus derivadas primeras/segundas son finitas y suaves en los intervalos relevantes r ∈ (rH+ε, Rmax)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def test_smoothness(r, dV):\n",
        "    # Derivadas numéricas central\n",
        "    dV_prime = np.gradient(dV, r)\n",
        "    dV_second = np.gradient(dV_prime, r)\n",
        "    contains_nan = np.isnan(dV).any() or np.isnan(dV_prime).any() or np.isnan(dV_second).any()\n",
        "    max_grad = np.max(np.abs(dV_prime))\n",
        "    max_second = np.max(np.abs(dV_second))\n",
        "    return {'nan': contains_nan, 'max_grad': float(max_grad), 'max_second': float(max_second)}\n",
        "\n",
        "smoothness_summary = {}\n",
        "for a in a_list:\n",
        "    rH = r_plus(M, a)\n",
        "    r = np.linspace(rH + 1e-6, 100, 5000)\n",
        "    dV = deltaV_real(r, rH)\n",
        "    smoothness_summary[str(a)] = test_smoothness(r, dV)\n",
        "\n",
        "smoothness_summary"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Test 2 — Límites físicos (horizonte y asintótico)\n",
        "Comprobamos que δV(r→rH) y δV(r→∞) tienden a valores finitos y adecuados (cercanos a 0 en nuestros modelos físicos)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def test_limits(a):\n",
        "    rH = r_plus(M, a)\n",
        "    r_near = rH + 1e-6\n",
        "    v_near = float(deltaV_real(np.array([r_near]), rH))\n",
        "    r_far = 1e6\n",
        "    v_far = float(deltaV_real(np.array([r_far]), rH))\n",
        "    return {'rH': rH, 'dV_near_horizon': v_near, 'dV_at_infty': v_far}\n",
        "\n",
        "limits_summary = {str(a): test_limits(a) for a in a_list}\n",
        "limits_summary"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Test 3 — Test de escala (homogeneidad dimensional)\n",
        "Comprobamos que si rescalamos M→λM y r→λr la forma de δV en unidades adimensionales es consistente (comprobación de invariancia por escala geométrica)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def scale_test(lambda_scale=2.5, a=0.5):\n",
        "    M1 = 1.0\n",
        "    rH1 = r_plus(M1, a)\n",
        "    r1 = np.linspace(rH1+1e-6, 100, 5000)\n",
        "    dV1 = deltaV_real(r1, rH1)\n",
        "    # Rescale\n",
        "    M2 = M1 * lambda_scale\n",
        "    rH2 = r_plus(M2, a * lambda_scale)  # espín escala formal (toy)\n",
        "    r2 = r1 * lambda_scale\n",
        "    dV2 = deltaV_real(r2, rH2)\n",
        "    # Reescalamos dV2 a la malla r1 (interpolación) y comparamos formas relativas\n",
        "    from scipy.interpolate import interp1d\n",
        "    f = interp1d(r2, dV2, kind='cubic', bounds_error=False, fill_value='extrapolate')\n",
        "    dV2_on_r1 = f(r1)\n",
        "    rel_diff = np.nanmean(np.abs((dV1 - dV2_on_r1) / np.maximum(1e-12, np.abs(dV1))))\n",
        "    return rel_diff\n",
        "\n",
        "scale_diff = scale_test(3.0, a=0.5)\n",
        "scale_diff"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Test 4 — Consistencia con Regge–Wheeler: no introducir nuevos pozos peligrosos\n",
        "Comparamos V_RW(r) y V_RW(r)+δV(r) para asegurarnos que no aparecen pozos profundos ni singularidades que invaliden la aproximación QNM."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def V_RW(r, l=2, M=1.0):\n",
        "    return (1 - 2*M / r) * (l*(l+1) / r**2 - 6*M / r**3)\n",
        "\n",
        "def rw_consistency_test(a=0.7):\n",
        "    rH = r_plus(M, a)\n",
        "    r = np.linspace(rH + 1e-3, 100, 5000)\n",
        "    V = V_RW(r)\n",
        "    dV = deltaV_real(r, rH)\n",
        "    Vtot = V + dV\n",
        "    # Encontrar mínimos y máximos locales\n",
        "    from scipy.signal import argrelextrema\n",
        "    maxima = argrelextrema(V, np.greater)[0]\n",
        "    maxima_tot = argrelextrema(Vtot, np.greater)[0]\n",
        "    # Comprobación básica: el máximo principal debe mantenerse cerca\n",
        "    if len(maxima) == 0 or len(maxima_tot) == 0:\n",
        "        return {'ok': False, 'reason': 'no maxima found'}\n",
        "    rmax = r[maxima[0]]\n",
        "    rmax_tot = r[maxima_tot[0]]\n",
        "    return {'rmax': float(rmax), 'rmax_tot': float(rmax_tot), 'delta_rmax': float(abs(rmax - rmax_tot))}\n",
        "\n",
        "rw_test = rw_consistency_test(a=0.7)\n",
        "rw_test"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Test 5 — Robustez numérica (mallas: 1k, 10k, 100k)\n",
        "Comprobamos NaNs, infs y tiempos razonables de evaluación para distintas mallas."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "robust = {}\n",
        "for n in mallas:\n",
        "    rH = r_plus(M, 0.5)\n",
        "    r = np.linspace(rH + 1e-6, 500, n)\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        dV = deltaV_real(r, rH)\n",
        "        has_nan = np.isnan(dV).any()\n",
        "        has_inf = np.isinf(dV).any()\n",
        "        max_abs = float(np.max(np.abs(dV)))\n",
        "        robust[n] = {'nan': bool(has_nan), 'inf': bool(has_inf), 'max_abs': max_abs}\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        robust[n] = {'error': str(e)}\n",
        "\n",
        "robust"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Test 6 — Convergencia de la integral perturbativa para δω con refinamiento de malla\n",
        "Evaluamos I = ∫ Ψ₀ δV Ψ₀ dr en mallas crecientes y comprobamos convergencia del resultado."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def compute_deltaomega_convergence(nlist=[2000,5000,10000]):\n",
        "    rH = r_plus(M, 0.7)\n",
        "    results_conv = {}\n",
        "    for n in nlist:\n",
        "        r = np.linspace(rH + 1e-3, rH + 80, n)\n",
        "        psi = normalize_psi(r, psi0(r, rH))\n",
        "        dV = deltaV_real(r, rH)\n",
        "        I = simps(psi * dV * psi, r)\n",
        "        results_conv[n] = float(I)\n",
        "    return results_conv\n",
        "\n",
        "conv_results = compute_deltaomega_convergence([2000,5000,10000,20000])\n",
        "conv_results"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Test 7 — Histogramas y signo\n",
        "Verificamos si δV cambia de signo y cuál es su distribución de valores (esto es importante para interpretar si es attractiva/repulsiva localmente)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "rH = r_plus(M, 0.5)\n",
        "r = np.linspace(rH + 1e-3, 200, 5000)\n",
        "dV_sample = deltaV_real(r, rH)\n",
        "neg_frac = float(np.sum(dV_sample < 0)) / len(dV_sample)\n",
        "pos_frac = float(np.sum(dV_sample > 0)) / len(dV_sample)\n",
        "stats = {'neg_frac': neg_frac, 'pos_frac': pos_frac, 'min': float(np.min(dV_sample)), 'max': float(np.max(dV_sample))}\n",
        "stats\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Visualizaciones finales\n",
        "1) δV(r) con V_RW\n",
        "2) δV' (derivada) para inspección\n",
        "3) Heatmap de δV para parámetros (η, kflow) si procede"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "rH = r_plus(M, 0.7)\n",
        "r = np.linspace(rH + 1e-3, 200, 5000)\n",
        "V = V_RW(r)\n",
        "dV = deltaV_real(r, rH)\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(7,4))\n",
        "plt.plot(r, V, label='V_RW')\n",
        "plt.plot(r, V + dV, label='V_RW + δV')\n",
        "plt.plot(r, dV, label='δV', alpha=0.7)\n",
        "plt.xlim(rH, 50)\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.title('Potenciales: Regge-Wheeler y corrección EDR')\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(7,3))\n",
        "dVprime = np.gradient(dV, r)\n",
        "plt.plot(r, dVprime)\n",
        "plt.xlim(rH, 50)\n",
        "plt.title('Derivada numérica d(δV)/dr')\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Guardado de resumen de resultados de tests\n",
        "Se guarda en `results/tests_deltaV_summary.json` para trazabilidad."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "os.makedirs('results', exist_ok=True)\n",
        "summary = {\n",
        "    'smoothness': smoothness_summary,\n",
        "    'limits': limits_summary,\n",
        "    'scale_diff': float(scale_diff),\n",
        "    'rw_test': rw_test,\n",
        "    'robustness': robust,\n",
        "    'convergence': conv_results,\n",
        "    'hist_stats': stats\n",
        "}\n",
        "with open('results/tests_deltaV_summary.json', 'w') as f:\n",
        "    json.dump(summary, f, indent=2)\n",
        "\n",
        "print('Resumen guardado en results/tests_deltaV_summary.json')\n",
        "summary"
      ]
    },
    {
